From: Jacob Keller <jacob.e.keller@intel.com>
Date: Fri, 18 Oct 2013 05:09:19 +0000
Subject: ixgbe: show <2% for encoding loss on PCIe Gen3
Patch-mainline: v3.13-rc1
Git-commit: 9f0a433ce69d63ae2c45ef801b9b1d8967165350
References: bug#908398 FATE#317382

This patch updates the ixgbe_check_minimum_link function to correctly show that
there is some minor loss of encoding, even though we don't calculate it in the
max GT/s equation. It is small enough to not bother, but is better to report it
than not.

Signed-off-by: Jacob Keller <jacob.e.keller@intel.com>
Tested-by: Phil Schmitt <phillip.j.schmitt@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Jeff Kirsher <jeffrey.t.kirsher@intel.com>
Acked-by: Benjamin Poirier <bpoirier@suse.de>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ixgbe/ixgbe_main.c |    4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ixgbe/ixgbe_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ixgbe/ixgbe_main.c
@@ -249,7 +249,7 @@ static void ixgbe_check_minimum_link(str
 		max_gts = 4 * width;
 		break;
 	case PCIE_SPEED_8_0GT:
-		/* 128b/130b encoding only reduces throughput by 1% */
+		/* 128b/130b encoding reduces throughput by less than 2% */
 		max_gts = 8 * width;
 		break;
 	default:
@@ -267,7 +267,7 @@ static void ixgbe_check_minimum_link(str
 		   width,
 		   (speed == PCIE_SPEED_2_5GT ? "20%" :
 		    speed == PCIE_SPEED_5_0GT ? "20%" :
-		    speed == PCIE_SPEED_8_0GT ? "N/a" :
+		    speed == PCIE_SPEED_8_0GT ? "<2%" :
 		    "Unknown"));
 
 	if (max_gts < expected_gts) {
